latestIgtvVideos.title: Self love not selfie
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
Filtered selfies shouldn't measure your "self-esteem" or "self-confidence" ❤️

It is no one, but only you who needs to shed these inhibitions and emerge victorious through this world of filtered perfection 🙆🏽‍♀‍

Hand in hand with Dove's Self Esteem Project and IAGT India, let us aim to break all the plastic beauty standards and stereotypes and create a world where people can feel free to grow up confidently and be empowered to love and accept themselves as whole.

Taking inspiration from my personal turmoil, here is a small note by me, where I speak about how Self-love is above a filtered selfie for #ItsAGirlThingIndia Presented by @dove

If you believe in self-love, I too believe in you. 
Share your poem or your story on "Love Yourself Not Your Filtered Selfie" without using any filters, 
Tag @iagtindia @dove and use the hashtag #LoveMyUnfilteredSelfie
The best three will entries get featured on @iagtindia page!! 🌟

latestIgtvVideos.title: Insurance nahi assurance
latestIgtvVideos.caption:
We all have aspirations and a plan to navigate through life with a smile. While some might want to buy a car, some build a home, have a business or just a healthy family life. But life is unpredictable and we never know what it brings along. 
Why not secure these aspirations when you have the chance, so unforeseen circumstances cannot turn your smile upside down.

This National Insurance Awareness Day, SBI General Insurance (@sbigeneral ) along with India Film Project (@indiafilmproject ) takes this opportunity to remind you, that life might be uncertain but you can secure what you value with general insurance.

latestPosts.caption:
Have you ever told your father how much you love him? :’) 

• To me this isn’t just a watch. It wraps around my wrist but it’s not made of metal… it feels like it’s made of words. Words my father could never say out loud : that he loves me, that he’s proud of me! 
And every time I wear it, I quietly whisper back “I love you too yaar Papa!”
I let my words drift into the air, hoping they’ll somehow find their way to Papa… until I can find the courage to say those words to him myself. I hope I will tell him how much I love him someday… <3

#fathersday #fatherlove #middleclassfamily #storytelling #stories
